<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 28 at 8:28AM CDT  by NWS Mobile</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Stone County through
915 AM CDT...
At 828 AM CDT, National Weather Service doppler radar indicated a
strong thunderstorm 13 miles north of Kiln, or 14 miles north of
Diamondhead, moving northeast at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Wiggins, Perkinston and McHenry.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
